assign numbers as array = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6};

$ Basic slicing
$ From index 1 to 4 (end excluded)
show method:array numbers.slice["1:4"];  $ Output: {2, 3, 4}

$ Omitting values
$ Start omitted (beginning → end)
show method:array numbers.slice[":3"];  $ Output: {1, 2, 3}

$ End omitted (start → end)
show method:array numbers.slice["3:"];  $ Output: {4, 5, 6}

$ Using step (`::`)
$ Every second element
show method:array numbers.slice["::2"];  $ Output: {1, 3, 5}

$ Every third element
show method:array numbers.slice["::3"];  $ Output: {1, 4}

$ Reverse slicing (negative step)
$ Reverse the array
show method:array numbers.slice["::-1"];  $ Output: {6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1}

$ Reverse with step
show method:array numbers.slice["::-2"];  $ Output: {6, 4, 2}

$ Mixed slicing
$ Slice a range with step
show method:array numbers.slice["1:6:2"];  $ Output: {2, 4, 6}